```{.r .cell-code}
personal_details_name <- names(cancer_data)[c(22,11,25,27,45,46)]

personal_details <- cancer_data %>% 
  select(all_of(personal_details_name))

## creating categories for age 
personal_details <- personal_details %>%
  mutate(age_groups = cut(age,
                          breaks = c(18, 28, 38, 48, 58, 68),
                          labels = c("18 - 28", "29 - 38", "39 - 48", "49 - 58", "59 - 68"),
                          include.lowest = TRUE))

personal_details <- personal_details %>%
  mutate(across(c(county, education, religion, insurance, instype), ~ as_factor(.)))

personal_details$religion <- recode(personal_details$religion,
                            "Christian catholic" ="Christian",
                            "Christian protestant" ="Christian",
                            "Christian evangelist" ="Christian")
personal_details$religion <- droplevels(personal_details$religion)

## recoding the education factors
personal_details$education <- recode(personal_details$education,
                                     "refuses to respond" = "Others",
                                     "doesn't know" = "Others",
                                     "NA" = "Others")
personal_details$education <- droplevels(personal_details$education)

personal_details$education[personal_details$education == "NA"] <- NA
personal_details$instype[personal_details$instype == "NA"] <- NA
personal_details$insurance[personal_details$insurance == "9999"] <- NA


table1 <- personal_details %>% 
  select(age,age_groups,county,education,religion,insurance,instype)
```

```{.r .cell-code}
# 1. summarize data of personal details
gt_table1 <- tbl_summary(table1,
                        missing = "ifany",
                        label = list(
                          age ~ "Age",
                          age_groups ~ "Age groups",
                          education ~ "Education Level",
                          religion ~ "Religion",
                          insurance ~ "Covered by Insuarance",
                          instype ~ "Insurance Type",
                          county ~ "District"),
                        statistic = list(age ~ "{median} ({IQR})")
                        ) %>% 
  modify_header(label = "**Variable**") %>% 
  bold_labels()
gt_table1
```

```{.r .cell-code}
## 2. Summarize the data of maritals status
marital_status_names <- names(cancer_data)[c(34,36,37,38,39)]

## selecting th relevant variables for marital status
marital_status <- cancer_data %>% 
  select(all_of(marital_status_names))

marital_status <- marital_status %>%
  mutate(across(c(marital_status,partnership_duration,partner_livewith,polygynous), ~ as_factor(.)))

marital_status <- marital_status %>% 
  mutate(
    age_group = case_when(
      agemarit >= 18 & agemarit <= 28 ~ "18 - 28",
      agemarit > 28 & agemarit <= 38 ~ "29 - 38",
      agemarit > 18 & agemarit <= 48 ~ "39 - 48",
      agemarit > 18 & agemarit <= 58 ~ "49 - 58",
      agemarit > 18 & agemarit <= 68 ~ "59 - 68",
    )
  )

## recoding the marital status partner living duartion factors
marital_status$partnership_duration <- recode(marital_status$partnership_duration,
                                              "9904" = "Others",
                                              "9999" = "Others")
marital_status$partnership_duration <- droplevels(marital_status$partnership_duration)

marital_status$marital_status <- recode(marital_status$marital_status,
                                              "9999" = "Others")
marital_status$partnership_duration <- droplevels(marital_status$partnership_duration)

marital_status$partner_livewith <- recode(marital_status$partner_livewith,
                                        "9999" = "Others",
                                        "9905" = "Others")
marital_status$partner_livewith <- droplevels(marital_status$partner_livewith)

marital_status$polygynous <- recode(marital_status$polygynous,
                                          "9999" = "Others",
                                          "9906" = "Others")
marital_status$polygynous <- droplevels(marital_status$polygynous)


table2 <- marital_status %>% 
  select("age_group","marital_status","partnership_duration","partner_livewith","polygynous")

# 2.1. summarize data of marital status details details
gt_table2 <- tbl_summary(table2,
                        missing = "ifany",
                        by = age_group,
                        label = list(
                          age_group = "Age Married",
                          marital_status = "Marital Status",
                          partnership_duration = "Duration in marriage or relationship",
                          partner_livewith = "Live with patner",
                          polygynous = "Polygnous")
                      ) %>% 
  add_p() %>% 
  modify_spanning_header(c(stat_1,stat_2) ~ "**Age Groups**") %>% 
  modify_header(label ~ "**Variable**") %>% 
  bold_labels() %>% 
  modify_footnote(starts_with("stat_") ~ "Median (IQR) or Frequency (%)")
```

```{.r .cell-code}
## 3. House hold details
household_names <- names(cancer_data)[c(29,32)]

## selecting th relevant variables for marital status
household_details <- cancer_data %>% 
  select(all_of(household_names))

household_details <- household_details %>%
  mutate(across(c(rel_hh), ~ as_factor(.)))

household_details <- household_details %>% 
  mutate(
    size = case_when(
      nb_household >= 1 & nb_household <= 3 ~ "1 - 3",
      nb_household >= 4 & nb_household <= 6 ~ "4 - 6",
      nb_household >= 7 ~ "7+"
    )
  )

household_details$rel_hh <- recode(household_details$rel_hh,
                                        "9999" = "Others")
household_details$rel_hh <- droplevels(household_details$rel_hh)

table3 <- household_details %>% 
  select("size","nb_household","rel_hh")

# 2.1. summarize data of marital status details details
gt_table3 <- tbl_summary(
  table3,
  statistic = list(nb_household ~ "Mean: {mean} SD: ({sd})"),
  label = list(
    size = "Household Size",
    nb_household = "Household Size(Mean and Sd)",
    rel_hh = "Household head"
  )
) %>% 
  modify_header(label ~ "**Variables**") %>% 
  bold_labels()
gt_table3
```

```{.r .cell-code}
## visualizing what district has most house hold members using ggplot2
size_county_names <- names(cancer_data)[c(11,29)]

## selecting the relevant variables for visualizing
size_county <- cancer_data %>% 
  select(all_of(size_county_names))

size_county <- size_county %>% 
  mutate(
    size = case_when(
      nb_household >= 1 & nb_household <= 3 ~ "1 - 3",
      nb_household >= 4 & nb_household <= 6 ~ "4 - 6",
      nb_household >= 7 ~ "7+"
    )
  )

size_county <- size_county %>%
  mutate(across(c(county,size), ~ as_factor(.)))

size_county <- size_county %>% 
  select(!nb_household)

size_county <- size_county %>% 
  group_by(size) %>% # Variable to be transformed
  count() %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(perc = `n` / sum(`n`)) %>% 
  arrange(perc) %>%
  mutate(labels = scales::percent(perc))

piechart_hhsize <- ggplot(size_county, aes(x = "", y = perc, fill = size)) +
  geom_col(color = "black") +
  geom_label(aes(label = paste(n,",",labels)), color = c(1, "white", "white"),
             position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5),
             show.legend = FALSE) +
  guides(fill = guide_legend(title = "Household Size")) +
  scale_fill_viridis_d() +
  coord_polar(theta = "y") + 
  theme_void()

piechart_hhsize
```

```{.r .cell-code}
## prevalence of CC Screening and service use


## knowledge score generation
knowledge_names <- names(cancer_data)[c(223,225,239,241)]

## selecting th relevant variables for marital status
knowledge_score_dits <- cancer_data %>% 
  select(all_of(knowledge_names))

knowledge_score_dits <- knowledge_score_dits %>%
  mutate(across(c(heardcc,problemcc,availscreencc,symptscc), ~ as_factor(.)))

knowledge_score_dits <-  knowledge_score_dits %>% 
  mutate(
    heardcc_score = case_when(
      heardcc == "no" ~ 0,
      heardcc == "yes" ~ 1
    ),
    problemcc_score = case_when(
      problemcc == "no" ~ 0,
      problemcc == "yes" ~ 1
    ),
    availscreencc_score = case_when(
      availscreencc == "no" ~ 0,
      availscreencc == "yes" ~ 1
    ),
    symptscc_score = case_when(
      symptscc == "no" ~ 0,
      symptscc == "yes" ~ 1
    )
  ) %>% 
  mutate(total_score = rowSums(select(., ends_with("_score")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  mutate(
    total_score_category = case_when(
      total_score >= 0 & total_score <= 1 ~ "Low knowledge",
      total_score == 2 ~ "Moderate knowledge",
      total_score >= 3 & total_score <= 4 ~ "High knowledge"
    )
  )

table4 <- knowledge_score_dits %>% 
  select(total_score_category)

gt_table4 <- table4 %>% 
  tbl_summary(
    label = list(
      total_score_category = "Knowledge Score"
    )
  ) %>% 
  modify_header(label = "**Knowledge Score**") %>% 
  bold_labels()

gt_table4
```
